description:
complete_multipart_upload (L725-797) holds a DashMap RefMut across the entire validation loop (L752-765) AND the concatenation loop (L769-773). This blocks any concurrent upload_part or abort_multipart_upload on the same upload_id for the full duration.

**Fix:** Collect all part data into Vec<u8> during the validation loop, then drop(upload) before computing the final ETag and inserting the completed object. This reduces lock hold time from O(data_size) to O(validation_only).

**Location:** crates/cirrus-s3/src/storage.rs L768-773

```rust
// Current: double-read through RefMut
let mut all_data: Vec<u8> = Vec::new();
for part in parts {
    // ... validation ...
    if let Some(stored) = upload.parts.get(&part.part_number) {
        all_data.extend_from_slice(&stored.data);
    }
}

// Better: collect during validation, then drop
let mut all_data: Vec<u8> = Vec::new();
for part in parts {
    // ... validation + collect ...
    all_data.extend_from_slice(&stored.data);
}
drop(upload); // Now safe to release before ETag computation
```

Discovered during PR #5 review. Depends on cirrus-qhv (Phase 3 storage).

list_objects_v2 (L498-641) uses key[prefix.len()..] at L574 which will panic if a key is shorter than prefix length. The starts_with filter at L517 should prevent this, but if the DashMap is mutated between iteration and processing (concurrent put_object adding a key that races with the iteration), the invariant could break.

**Location:** crates/cirrus-s3/src/storage.rs L574

**Fix:** Use .get(prefix.len()..) with a guard, or accept as safe because starts_with guarantees key.len() >= prefix.len() for the in-memory case.

```rust
// Current (panics if key < prefix.len())
let remaining = &key[prefix.len()..];

// Safer
let remaining = key.get(prefix.len()..)?;
```

Discovered during PR #5 review. Depends on cirrus-qhv.
